In November 1989, the great Berlin wall came down. In 1990, the treaty reuniting both Germanies was signed, establishing October 3, as a Day of National Unity.German ambassador Jutta Frasch last week held a cocktail to celebrate the country s National Day, commemorating 26 years of reunification. A similar event was held in Nairobi and the envoy said they had to hold another in Mombasa because many Germans stay there.Present at the cocktail held at Tamarind Hotel was Mombasa governor Hassan Joho, nominated senator Emma Mbura and Mombasa education executive Lewa Mtana attended.